{"id":"MFN_M05","msgStructId":"MFN_M05","eventDesc":"Patient Location Master File Notification","description":"This section is specifically concerned with describing a master file message that should be used to transmit information which identifies the inventory of healthcare patient locations, such as nursing units, rooms, beds, clinics, exam rooms, etc.  In a network environment, this segment can be used to define patient locations to other applications.  The segment also includes the readiness states and support locations for the patient locations.\r\n\r\nThe LOC, LCH, LRL, LDP, and LCC segments must be preceded by the MFI and MFE segments, as described in Section 8.5, \"GENERAL MASTER FILE SEGMENTS.\"  In the following message, the MFI-1 - Master File Identifier field should equal \"LOC\"","sample":null,"chapters":["CH_08"],"segments":[{"id":"MSH","name":"MSH","longName":"Message Header","sequence":"1","usage":"R","rpt":"1","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"SFT","name":"SFT","longName":"Software Segment","sequence":"2","usage":"O","rpt":"*","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"UAC","name":"UAC","longName":"User Authentication Credential","sequence":"3","usage":"O","rpt":"1","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"MFI","name":"MFI","longName":"Master File Identification","sequence":"4","usage":"R","rpt":"1","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":null,"name":"MF LOCATION","longName":null,"sequence":null,"usage":"R","rpt":"*","isGroup":true,"segments":[{"id":"MFE","name":"MFE","longName":"Master File Entry","sequence":"5","usage":"R","rpt":"1","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"LOC","name":"LOC","longName":"Location Identification","sequence":"6","usage":"R","rpt":"1","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"LCH","name":"LCH","longName":"Location Characteristic","sequence":"7","usage":"O","rpt":"*","isGroup":false,"segments":null},{"id":"LRL","name":"LRL","longName":"Location Relationship","sequence":"8","usage":"O","rpt":"*","isGroup":false,"segments"